Privacy Policy for NotiXel

Last Updated: October 4, 2025

1. Introduction

NotiXel ("we," "our," or "us") operates the NotiXel application, which provides bi-directional synchronization services between Microsoft Excel/OneDrive and Notion databases. This page informs you of our policies regarding the collection, use, and disclosure of personal data when you use our Service and the choices you have associated with that data.

We use your data to provide and improve the Service. By using the Service, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.

2. Information We Collect and Use

We collect two types of information:

Personal Identification Information (PII)

  • Email Address: Collected during the Microsoft OAuth process for user identification and communication.
  • User ID: A unique identifier assigned to you by our system.

Integration Credentials (Access Tokens)

To perform the synchronization, we require access to your third-party accounts. **We do not store your raw passwords.** We store securely generated tokens:

  • Microsoft Refresh and Access Tokens: Used to access your OneDrive files (specifically, the Excel sheets you explicitly select) and refresh your access to Microsoft services.
  • Notion API Key: Used to read and write data to the Notion databases you share with our integration.

Data Processing Scope: NotiXel only accesses and processes data from the specific Notion databases and Excel files/worksheets that you explicitly select for synchronization. We do not access other files or databases in your accounts.

3. Use of Data

NotiXel uses the collected data for various purposes:

  • To provide and maintain the Service (Synchronization).
  • To manage your account and monitor your usage limits (e.g., maximum auto-sync jobs).
  • To detect, prevent, and address technical issues.
  • To notify you about changes to our Service.

4. Security of Data

The security of your data is important to us. We implement industry-standard security measures, including HTTPS/TLS and encryption for stored tokens (where feasible), to protect your credentials. However, no method of transmission over the Internet or method of electronic storage is 100% secure.

If you delete your NotiXel account, all associated tokens and PII will be removed from our database.

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and updating the "Last Updated" date.

Contact Us: support@notixel.com
